      Evergrande
   =20
 =20
I guess that if you are a financial regulator there is something to be said=
 for taking an inscrutable tough-love approach with companies that run into=
 trouble:Company: We are almost out of money and have so many creditors. Sh=
ould we prioritize delivering product to customers, or paying suppliers, or=
 making payments on debt to local retail investors, or making payments on d=
ebt to offshore bond investors?Regulator: Yes.Company: ...Regulator: ...Com=
pany: Okay, good one, ha ha ha,=C2=A0but seriously we can=E2=80=99t pay eve=
ryone.Regulator: Try.What is the benefit, to the regulator, of saying =E2=
=80=9Cif I were you I=E2=80=99d pay the retail investors and stiff the offs=
hore ones=E2=80=9D? Why would you want to sound like you approve of stiffin=
g anyone?=C2=A0You=C2=A0want=C2=A0the company to feel bad about all of this=
, to be nervous; you don=E2=80=99t want to be too quick to bless a plan to =
wriggle out of any debts.=C2=A0I=E2=80=99m not sure that that=E2=80=99s exa=
ctly what  this is, though it kind of sounds like it:Financial regulators i=
n Beijing issued a broad set of instructions to China Evergrande Group, tel=
ling the embattled developer to focus on completing unfinished properties a=
nd repaying individual investors while avoiding a near-term default on doll=
ar bonds.In a recent meeting with Evergrande representatives, regulators sa=
id the company should communicate proactively with bondholders to avoid a d=
efault but didn=E2=80=99t give more specific guidance, a person familiar wi=
th the matter said. The developer has an $83.5 million coupon due Thursday,=
 with a 30-day grace period to make the payment.There=E2=80=99s no indicati=
on that regulators offered financial support to Evergrande for the bond pay=
ment, and it=E2=80=99s unclear whether officials believe the company should=
 eventually impose losses on offshore creditors. Policy makers are trying t=
o learn more about who holds Evergrande=E2=80=99s bonds, the person said, a=
sking not to be identified discussing sensitive information.Focus on delive=
ring properties to customers and paying individual investors, but don=E2=80=
=99t default on your offshore bonds either. Just try not to be in trouble a=
nymore? I guess =E2=80=9Cavoiding near-term default on dollar bonds=E2=80=
=9D is the softest ask there. =E2=80=9CGet dollar bondholders not to compla=
in for a couple of weeks, then default on them=E2=80=9D is one possible int=
erpretation of that one. If you are a dollar bondholder and Evergrande call=
s you after this meeting to say =E2=80=9Chey just give us two weeks and we=
=E2=80=99ll have your money,=E2=80=9D do you believe them?
